cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with modeling social interaction networks and inferring user communities and interests based on social media interactions. The paper discusses the application of such networks for effective dissemination of information towards planning large-scale events. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Development). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques to analyze social media conversations, which falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of network algorithms to single out specific nodes in a given community, which falls under the sub-categories cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
